1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:15,782
We're starting to see

2
00:00:15,849 --> 00:00:18,885
some new faces here on <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

3
00:00:18,952 --> 00:00:20,453
We have someone new with us.

4
00:00:22,589 --> 00:00:23,990
A NEW CHEF BURSTING ON TO THE SHOW

5
00:00:24,057 --> 00:00:26,659
She secured her presence
on <i>Culinary Class Wars 2</i>

6
00:00:26,726 --> 00:00:29,662
with the nickname Little Tiger.

7
00:00:29,729 --> 00:00:30,730
I'm Little Tiger.

8
00:00:30,797 --> 00:00:32,432
-Little?
-Tiger. Rawr.

9
00:00:32,499 --> 00:00:33,633
LITTLE TIGER

10
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:35,335
<i>Little chef who loves Korean cuisine,</i>

11
00:00:35,402 --> 00:00:37,404
<i>please welcome Chef Kim Si-hyeon!</i>

12
00:00:37,470 --> 00:00:39,839
Welcome to the show.

13
00:00:39,906 --> 00:00:40,907
WELCOME

14
00:00:41,474 --> 00:00:42,609
Say hi to her.

15
00:00:42,675 --> 00:00:46,780
Please look into the camera
and say hello to our viewers.

16
00:00:46,846 --> 00:00:48,548
Hello, I'm Kim Si-hyeon,

17
00:00:48,615 --> 00:00:50,650
also known as Little Tiger.

18
00:00:50,717 --> 00:00:52,318
It's great to be here.

19
00:00:52,385 --> 00:00:53,620
I'm so nervous!

20
00:00:54,187 --> 00:00:55,622
WELCOMING HER WITH A RAWR!

21
00:00:55,688 --> 00:00:57,123
-I'm so nervous!
-You are?

22
00:00:57,190 --> 00:00:58,825
She kept saying that in the green room.

23
00:00:58,892 --> 00:01:00,727
-She was so nervous.
-It was driving her crazy.

24
00:01:00,794 --> 00:01:03,096
-It's an emergency.
-Yes?

25
00:01:03,163 --> 00:01:04,664
Sung-jun doesn't look so well today.

26
00:01:04,731 --> 00:01:06,066
-What's up?
-What is it, Sung-jun?

27
00:01:06,132 --> 00:01:07,700
-What?
-He's been looking gloomy all day.

28
00:01:07,767 --> 00:01:09,602
As I mentioned previously,

29
00:01:09,669 --> 00:01:10,870
-it's an emergency.
-Is it?

30
00:01:10,937 --> 00:01:14,140
-Too many are after this. Yes.
-You were worried about this.

31
00:01:14,207 --> 00:01:16,109
I'll watch and see how good she is.

32
00:01:16,843 --> 00:01:19,312
He's a typical guy
who hates seeing others do well.

33
00:01:19,379 --> 00:01:20,647
Cut it out. She's nervous.

34
00:01:20,713 --> 00:01:23,216
-You may lose your spot.
-Don't be pathetic!

35
00:01:23,283 --> 00:01:24,484
HMPH

36
00:01:24,551 --> 00:01:26,419
Chef Si-hyeon told us that

37
00:01:26,486 --> 00:01:28,555
she grew up watching this show.

38
00:01:28,621 --> 00:01:30,523
-I see.
-I grew up with the show,

39
00:01:30,590 --> 00:01:33,460
so when I first began cooking,

40
00:01:33,526 --> 00:01:36,729
I thought of everyone here as role models.

41
00:01:37,564 --> 00:01:39,899
How old were you
when you began to watch us?

42
00:01:39,966 --> 00:01:41,868
I was born in 2000.

43
00:01:41,935 --> 00:01:43,670
-You were born in 2000?
-Yes.

44
00:01:43,736 --> 00:01:45,371
-Her ID number begins with 4.
-Really?

45
00:01:45,939 --> 00:01:46,940
SHE'S SO YOUNG

46
00:01:47,006 --> 00:01:49,342
-So she began watching in middle school.
-You're right.

47
00:01:49,409 --> 00:01:54,114
Was our show a part of the reason why
you participated in <i>Culinary Class Wars 2</i>?

48
00:01:54,180 --> 00:01:56,916
-I'd say so, yes.
-That is the case.

49
00:01:57,650 --> 00:01:58,985
-This show is big.
-Your dream began there.

50
00:01:59,052 --> 00:02:01,087
-Yes, of course.
-Among our chefs,

51
00:02:01,154 --> 00:02:04,290
-there is one particular chef…
-Is it me?

52
00:02:04,357 --> 00:02:06,092
…she looks up to as her hero.

53
00:02:06,159 --> 00:02:07,560
-He said, "Is it me?"
-Cut it out.

54
00:02:07,627 --> 00:02:09,662
HE'S LIKE, "IS IT ME?"

55
00:02:09,729 --> 00:02:12,599
-That chef is here right now.
-Who is it?

56
00:02:12,665 --> 00:02:15,201
It's Chef Sam Kim.

57
00:02:15,268 --> 00:02:16,870
A BIG SMILE

58
00:02:17,370 --> 00:02:18,738
THE BIGGEST SMILE HE HAS EVER SHOWN

59
00:02:18,805 --> 00:02:20,707
I saw his canine teeth very clearly!

60
00:02:20,773 --> 00:02:23,810
-I didn't know they were so big.
-Right?

61
00:02:23,877 --> 00:02:25,545
LITTLE TIGER'S ONE TRUE HERO

62
00:02:25,612 --> 00:02:29,015
-He's blushing!
-Since she was young.

63
00:02:29,082 --> 00:02:31,251
-It's really red.
-He's blushing.

64
00:02:31,317 --> 00:02:33,286
GOOD FOR YOU

65
00:02:33,620 --> 00:02:34,854
"SOMEONE" IS FLUTTERING HAPPILY

66
00:02:34,921 --> 00:02:36,756
Why don't you share
a word of encouragement?

67
00:02:36,823 --> 00:02:38,725
-Yes, talk to her.
-Relax and say something.

68
00:02:38,791 --> 00:02:41,161
You can tell me
if anyone tries to bully you.

69
00:02:42,495 --> 00:02:44,364
THE MOST LIKELY "SOMEONE"

70
00:02:44,430 --> 00:02:46,699
-What? I didn't get that.
-To tell him if anyone bullies her.

71
00:02:46,766 --> 00:02:49,269
Take care of yourself first!

72
00:02:49,335 --> 00:02:50,970
You get pushed around by everyone.

73
00:02:51,037 --> 00:02:53,673
How are you going to protect anyone else?

74
00:02:53,740 --> 00:02:56,042
-Right.
-You're way too nice.

75
00:02:56,109 --> 00:02:57,310
YOU'RE THE BEST!

76
00:02:57,377 --> 00:03:01,514
I hear Chef Jong-won also has
a word of advice from his heart.

77
00:03:01,581 --> 00:03:02,649
Take note of this.

78
00:03:02,715 --> 00:03:04,851
I have a few tips to help you survive.

79
00:03:04,918 --> 00:03:07,587
When you arrive in the morning,
the green room

80
00:03:07,654 --> 00:03:09,355
-is going to be quite hot.
-It's hot.

81
00:03:09,422 --> 00:03:10,657
FEELING CONSCIOUS

82
00:03:10,723 --> 00:03:12,392
Yes, it's steaming hot
because of a certain person.

83
00:03:12,458 --> 00:03:14,594
It's because of one person
who gets cold easily.

84
00:03:14,661 --> 00:03:17,397
-I've been dying of the heat.
-Never say that it's hot.

85
00:03:17,463 --> 00:03:19,799
-I see.
-You need to cool down on your own.

86
00:03:19,866 --> 00:03:23,369
And you'll also see weird people
who stare into the mirror

87
00:03:23,436 --> 00:03:26,506
-and suddenly begin to dance.
-Dancing?

88
00:03:26,573 --> 00:03:28,441
First, don't look them in the eyes.

89
00:03:28,508 --> 00:03:30,343
Second, don't talk to them.

90
00:03:30,410 --> 00:03:32,645
-He's right.
-Treat it like just another day.

91
00:03:32,712 --> 00:03:34,147
-You must hang in there.
-Okay.

92
00:03:34,214 --> 00:03:35,782
STAY STRONG THROUGH THIS BOOT CAMP

93
00:03:36,349 --> 00:03:38,885
Our guests today
are two people who love our show

94
00:03:38,952 --> 00:03:42,355
that come with the clearest eyes.

95
00:03:42,422 --> 00:03:44,624
Please welcome today's fridge owners!

96
00:03:44,691 --> 00:03:45,858
Come on out!

97
00:03:47,794 --> 00:03:48,795
Finally.

98
00:03:48,861 --> 00:03:51,631
Please welcome today's fridge owners.

99
00:03:53,199 --> 00:03:55,568
The two Korean Wave stars
beloved by Millennials and Gen Z,

100
00:03:55,635 --> 00:03:58,104
please welcome
An Yu-jin and Park Jin-young!

101
00:03:58,171 --> 00:04:00,039
Welcome to the show.

102
00:04:00,607 --> 00:04:03,209
GEN MZ FOLKS ARE EXCITED

103
00:04:03,276 --> 00:04:04,577
-Handsome and pretty.
-Come on in.

104
00:04:04,644 --> 00:04:06,579
Please welcome An Yu-jin of IVE!

105
00:04:07,747 --> 00:04:09,082
HOLY MOLY

106
00:04:10,316 --> 00:04:12,885
-You look way too happy today.
-I am.

107
00:04:13,620 --> 00:04:16,889
Hello, my name is An Yu-jin,
the leader of IVE.

108
00:04:17,957 --> 00:04:20,760
A BIG APPLAUSE

109
00:04:20,827 --> 00:04:22,495
She's beautiful.

110
00:04:22,562 --> 00:04:23,563
Let me introduce him.

111
00:04:23,630 --> 00:04:26,099
He owned the music industry
as a member of GOT7.

112
00:04:26,165 --> 00:04:27,934
ALSO HAS A SUCCESSFUL CAREER IN ACTING

113
00:04:28,001 --> 00:04:30,570
<i>Then he moved on to acting</i>
<i>and captured the screens too.</i>

114
00:04:31,104 --> 00:04:33,539
Please welcome actor Park Jin-young!

115
00:04:33,606 --> 00:04:34,707
Looking handsome!

116
00:04:35,508 --> 00:04:36,709
He looks so cool.

117
00:04:36,776 --> 00:04:38,411
He really is so cool.

118
00:04:38,478 --> 00:04:39,479
FLIPPING HER PONYTAIL

119
00:04:39,545 --> 00:04:41,914
We're so happy to have you two here.

120
00:04:41,981 --> 00:04:44,550
I hear you always wanted
to be on the show.

121
00:04:44,617 --> 00:04:47,353
It's the hottest program
as approved by the cast and the people.

122
00:04:47,420 --> 00:04:48,621
Do you really think so?

123
00:04:48,688 --> 00:04:50,023
HAHAHAHA

124
00:04:50,089 --> 00:04:51,424
So we are then.

125
00:04:51,491 --> 00:04:54,460
A BIG SMILE AFTER HER COMPLIMENT

126
00:04:54,527 --> 00:04:57,196
The show has dominated my algorithm,

127
00:04:57,263 --> 00:05:01,301
so I said I wanted to be on the show
after releasing our latest album,

128
00:05:01,367 --> 00:05:03,670
made my intentions clear,
and seized the opportunity.

129
00:05:03,736 --> 00:05:05,972
AND SEIZING THE SOLO SHOT

130
00:05:06,039 --> 00:05:09,208
Jin-young is also a huge fan of our show,

131
00:05:09,275 --> 00:05:11,077
that he even wanted
to barge into our studio.

132
00:05:11,144 --> 00:05:13,046
Did you want to burst into our shoot?

133
00:05:13,112 --> 00:05:15,348
-He's such a die-hard fan.
-Are you really?

134
00:05:15,415 --> 00:05:17,784
I was recently discharged
from military service,

135
00:05:17,850 --> 00:05:20,987
and I loved watching cooking shows
while I was in service.

136
00:05:21,054 --> 00:05:22,755
Yes, I heard it's loved by soldiers.

137
00:05:22,822 --> 00:05:24,157
Right. That's a year ago.

138
00:05:24,223 --> 00:05:27,627
Also, I starred in a drama on this network
until very recently,

139
00:05:27,694 --> 00:05:30,563
so I wanted to pull some strings,
visit, and take just a bite.

140
00:05:30,630 --> 00:05:31,931
During our shoot?

141
00:05:31,998 --> 00:05:33,833
-You're in a drama on the network?
-Yes.

142
00:05:33,900 --> 00:05:36,703
-It's called <i>Still Shining.</i>
<i>-Still Shining.</i>

143
00:05:36,769 --> 00:05:39,372
-It'll premiere on Friday, March 6th.
-<i>Still Shining.</i>

144
00:05:39,439 --> 00:05:41,341
<i>It'll begin airing at 8:50 p.m.</i>

145
00:05:41,407 --> 00:05:43,343
-Is that the premiere?
-It is.

146
00:05:43,409 --> 00:05:45,144
SHOW LOTS OF LOVE FOR STILL SHINING

147
00:05:45,211 --> 00:05:46,746
-Please show lots of love.
-It's soon.

148
00:05:46,813 --> 00:05:51,250
I heard Jin-young was quite concerned
about visiting with Yu-jin.

149
00:05:51,317 --> 00:05:53,086
I apologize for mentioning the army again.

150
00:05:53,152 --> 00:05:56,556
She's way too popular among soldiers, so…

151
00:05:56,622 --> 00:05:58,024
They're popular in the military.

152
00:05:58,091 --> 00:06:01,127
-Right.
-So my army buddies will probably say,

153
00:06:01,194 --> 00:06:03,696
"Who do you think you are
to be there with her?"

154
00:06:03,763 --> 00:06:04,931
CAN'T BELIEVE HIS CONNECTIONS

155
00:06:04,997 --> 00:06:06,599
-"Who do you…"
-They may think so.

156
00:06:06,666 --> 00:06:09,702
I know they'll be like,
"Who do you think you are to be there?"

157
00:06:09,769 --> 00:06:11,371
Your buddies will get jealous.

158
00:06:11,437 --> 00:06:14,507
Yu-jin, I also heard
you wanted to meet Jin-young

159
00:06:14,574 --> 00:06:17,443
to confirm something in real life.
What do you mean by this?

160
00:06:17,510 --> 00:06:20,279
Ever since my debut,
this is the first time I am…

161
00:06:20,346 --> 00:06:22,949
-It's our first time meeting.
-Yes, it's our first time.

162
00:06:23,015 --> 00:06:24,584
Back when I was a trainee,

163
00:06:24,650 --> 00:06:28,087
my agency often told me
that I looked exactly alike

164
00:06:28,154 --> 00:06:32,425
Jin-young when he dressed up as a girl.

165
00:06:32,492 --> 00:06:34,060
We got our hands on some photos,

166
00:06:34,127 --> 00:06:36,229
photos of Jin-young dressed up as a girl.

167
00:06:36,295 --> 00:06:37,363
Let's take a look.

168
00:06:38,398 --> 00:06:39,999
TA-DA

169
00:06:40,066 --> 00:06:41,901
-You're right.
-You're right!

170
00:06:41,968 --> 00:06:44,771
THEY HAVE SIMILAR FEATURES

171
00:06:44,837 --> 00:06:45,905
You're right.

172
00:06:45,972 --> 00:06:47,640
-The second one especially.
-I can see it.

173
00:06:47,707 --> 00:06:49,575
-I can see it.
-They look alike.

174
00:06:49,642 --> 00:06:53,146
-This is fascinating.
-It's something about their mouths.

175
00:06:53,813 --> 00:06:55,381
What are my army buddies going to say?

176
00:06:56,115 --> 00:06:58,584
WHO DO YOU THINK YOU ARE
TO BE KNOWN AS YU-JIN'S LOOK-ALIKE?

177
00:06:58,651 --> 00:07:01,154
Thank you so much, but they'll go, "Boo."

178
00:07:01,220 --> 00:07:03,089
Just ask for some autographs for them.

179
00:07:03,156 --> 00:07:04,891
-It's okay.
-It's okay?

180
00:07:04,957 --> 00:07:06,559
-They don't deserve it.
-I'll take one.

181
00:07:06,626 --> 00:07:09,529
Anyway, I have no idea what this is about,

182
00:07:09,595 --> 00:07:10,897
so I had to keep asking.

183
00:07:10,963 --> 00:07:14,467
When you call An Yu-jin,
you aren't supposed to call her An Yu-jin.

184
00:07:14,534 --> 00:07:16,869
-Why not?
-I have no idea what this means.

185
00:07:16,936 --> 00:07:18,404
You can't do that.

186
00:07:18,471 --> 00:07:19,639
-You can't.
-Why not?

187
00:07:19,705 --> 00:07:22,041
Why can't we call you An Yu-jin?
Isn't that your name?

188
00:07:22,108 --> 00:07:23,409
Are you actually Kim Yu-jin?

189
00:07:23,476 --> 00:07:25,244
There's something that always gets to me.

190
00:07:25,311 --> 00:07:26,679
Here's an example.

191
00:07:26,746 --> 00:07:30,750
People will go, Chef Hyun-suk,
Chef Poong, and Chef Kim.

192
00:07:30,817 --> 00:07:33,085
-Then what if they go…
-"Chef Kim"?

193
00:07:33,152 --> 00:07:34,821
Is Sam your surname?

194
00:07:35,521 --> 00:07:36,989
SCRATCH, SCRATCH

195
00:07:37,490 --> 00:07:38,825
IS KIM HIS FIRST NAME?

196
00:07:38,891 --> 00:07:40,026
Are you Sam or Kim?

197
00:07:40,092 --> 00:07:42,128
KIM OF THE SAM FAMILY

198
00:07:42,195 --> 00:07:44,230
Your example was wrong.

199
00:07:44,297 --> 00:07:45,431
EDITING OUT THE MOMENT

200
00:07:45,498 --> 00:07:46,666
Chef Sam.

201
00:07:46,732 --> 00:07:48,868
People will go, "Chef Sam," right?

202
00:07:48,935 --> 00:07:50,937
Then what if they suddenly go,
"Chef Son Jong-won"?

203
00:07:51,003 --> 00:07:52,438
How would you feel?

204
00:07:52,505 --> 00:07:54,740
I guess that's just how it is.

205
00:07:54,807 --> 00:07:55,775
-Is that okay?
-Yes.

206
00:07:55,842 --> 00:07:57,443
Not me.

207
00:07:57,510 --> 00:08:00,046
-This isn't what I was going for.
-That's just his name.

208
00:08:00,112 --> 00:08:04,951
People often talk to others
without mentioning their surnames.

209
00:08:05,017 --> 00:08:06,619
-Does it feel too formal?
-And then,

210
00:08:06,686 --> 00:08:09,622
when it comes to me,
my surname always sticks around.

211
00:08:09,689 --> 00:08:11,858
-I get what you mean.
-It's my first time here,

212
00:08:11,924 --> 00:08:14,126
but please call me Yu-jin
to feel more friendly.

213
00:08:14,193 --> 00:08:16,395
Can you call me just Yu-jin today?

214
00:08:16,462 --> 00:08:18,498
Now that I hear your story,
I can understand.

215
00:08:18,564 --> 00:08:20,700
We received a request from her,

216
00:08:20,766 --> 00:08:22,668
so Chef Kim, can you go first?

217
00:08:22,735 --> 00:08:24,637
Call her by her name.

218
00:08:24,704 --> 00:08:26,672
-Yu-jin.
-Yu-jin.

219
00:08:27,273 --> 00:08:28,608
CLAPS HAPPILY LIKE A SEAL

220
00:08:28,674 --> 00:08:29,775
He sounds so sweet.

221
00:08:31,277 --> 00:08:32,278
-So gentle.
-Jin-young.

222
00:08:32,345 --> 00:08:34,580
-You should befriend her, so try it.
-So sweet.

223
00:08:34,647 --> 00:08:36,349
-Yes.
-Yu-jin.

224
00:08:36,916 --> 00:08:38,484
YU-JIN

225
00:08:38,551 --> 00:08:39,819
Yes, Jin-young.

226
00:08:39,886 --> 00:08:41,220
PLEASE PUT THIS LINE IN A DRAMA

227
00:08:41,287 --> 00:08:43,789
-That was nice.
-He sounds so soft.

228
00:08:43,856 --> 00:08:45,024
It feels much friendlier.

229
00:08:45,091 --> 00:08:48,227
-I feel like we're friends already.
-I can see it.

230
00:08:48,294 --> 00:08:50,796
-I see.
-It feels like it.

231
00:08:50,863 --> 00:08:52,665
Do you want to give it a go, Sung-jun?

232
00:08:52,732 --> 00:08:54,033
-Yes, yes, yes.
-Okay.

233
00:08:54,934 --> 00:08:56,168
He loves it so much.

234
00:08:56,235 --> 00:08:58,237
HE'S SO DESPERATE

235
00:08:58,304 --> 00:09:00,439
Did you see that face?

236
00:09:00,506 --> 00:09:02,775
He has ulterior motives!

237
00:09:02,842 --> 00:09:05,711
<i>He pulled out his neck this far</i>
<i>and watched everything.</i>

238
00:09:05,778 --> 00:09:07,713
-It was as if you had been waiting.
-Yes!

239
00:09:07,780 --> 00:09:10,149
-Why are your ears so red?
-I've been watching.

240
00:09:10,216 --> 00:09:12,485
-I've never seen him so desperate.
-His ears are so red.

241
00:09:12,552 --> 00:09:14,620
SUNG-JUN FINALLY HAS A ROSY COMPLEXION

242
00:09:15,087 --> 00:09:16,422
LET'S MAKE HIS WISH COME TRUE

243
00:09:16,489 --> 00:09:17,723
Gosh, what an eyesore.

244
00:09:17,790 --> 00:09:20,426
Can you look at her and call her Yu-jin?

245
00:09:20,493 --> 00:09:22,261
Your face is making me so pissed.

246
00:09:22,828 --> 00:09:24,530
I'M TRYING TO GET IN THE MOOD

247
00:09:24,597 --> 00:09:26,899
-I'm dead serious.
-We'll give you a go sign.

248
00:09:26,966 --> 00:09:28,234
-Why are you serious?
-I can't watch.

249
00:09:28,301 --> 00:09:30,102
Get ready. Action!

250
00:09:30,169 --> 00:09:31,170
IN A SERIOUS MOOD

251
00:09:31,637 --> 00:09:33,339
LET'S HEAR WHAT HE'LL SAY

252
00:09:33,406 --> 00:09:35,041
Get ready. Action!

253
00:09:36,208 --> 00:09:37,610
Hey, Yu-jin. Do you like <i>malatang</i>?

254
00:09:40,146 --> 00:09:42,048
GO HAVE SOME BY YOURSELF, SUNG-JUN

255
00:09:42,114 --> 00:09:44,150
-How sad.
-He ruined it.

256
00:09:44,216 --> 00:09:45,217
THE WORST LINE EVER

257
00:09:45,284 --> 00:09:47,653
-That's hilarious.
-We gave him a chance, and he ruined it.

258
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:49,188
LINE, TIMING, FACE, ALL FAILED

259
00:09:49,255 --> 00:09:50,356
Don't take it that far.

260
00:09:50,423 --> 00:09:52,358
-Should've gone with Dubai chewy cookie.
-Relax.

261
00:09:52,425 --> 00:09:53,826
So do you prefer this vibe?

262
00:09:53,893 --> 00:09:56,963
-I love it.
-Make sure you leave out her surname.

263
00:09:57,029 --> 00:10:00,566
-We'll call you Yu-jin or Ms. Yu-jin.
-Please do that.

264
00:10:00,633 --> 00:10:04,904
I also heard there was something
she wanted to do with our chefs.

265
00:10:04,971 --> 00:10:06,138
Their performances

266
00:10:06,205 --> 00:10:09,008
are quite a sight here on the show, right?

267
00:10:09,075 --> 00:10:12,945
I really enjoyed
your rendition of "Queencard."

268
00:10:13,012 --> 00:10:15,281
-She saw that.
-Did you see "Queencard"?

269
00:10:15,348 --> 00:10:17,216
Yes, totally.

270
00:10:17,283 --> 00:10:21,053
I kept scrolling and scrolling,
but I only saw her doing "Queencard."

271
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:22,955
I couldn't miss it.

272
00:10:23,022 --> 00:10:25,124
And before that, there was "Fry."

273
00:10:25,191 --> 00:10:28,527
I really loved the dance
to your dish, "Fry."

274
00:10:28,594 --> 00:10:31,998
But none of the chefs
had danced to any of IVE's songs.

275
00:10:32,064 --> 00:10:33,633
-That's true.
-You're right.

276
00:10:33,699 --> 00:10:34,700
How did that happen?

277
00:10:34,767 --> 00:10:37,403
-It's a bit hard.
-I thought it was a shame.

278
00:10:37,470 --> 00:10:39,372
We'll release our album soon, so…

279
00:10:39,438 --> 00:10:42,541
It has to be done.
You have to do it. Do it.

280
00:10:42,608 --> 00:10:44,744
-Right.
-You can learn the dance on the spot.

281
00:10:44,810 --> 00:10:46,012
Yes, I can do that.

282
00:10:46,078 --> 00:10:47,313
I always did it on the spot.

283
00:10:47,380 --> 00:10:49,115
LOTS OF PRIDE FOR HIS DANCES

284
00:10:49,181 --> 00:10:52,084
Please show lots of love
for IVE's newest album.

285
00:10:52,151 --> 00:10:53,419
And now, it's time

286
00:10:53,486 --> 00:10:56,956
to go through IVE's leader
Yu-jin's fridge.

287
00:10:57,023 --> 00:11:00,326
We've already seen
a member of IVE's fridge before.

288
00:11:00,393 --> 00:11:02,194
<i>When we looked at Won-young's fridge…</i>

289
00:11:02,261 --> 00:11:04,597
What I love are dishes
that are creamy, rich, and cheesy.

290
00:11:04,664 --> 00:11:08,167
-Rich, creamy Vicky.
-<i>She said she liked rich, creamy dishes.</i>

291
00:11:08,234 --> 00:11:10,903
First of all, Won-young and I have
very different tastes in food.

292
00:11:10,970 --> 00:11:12,471
-They do.
-I'm someone

293
00:11:12,538 --> 00:11:14,840
who's into Korean cuisine,

294
00:11:14,907 --> 00:11:18,377
so I like to eat Korean food
even while traveling abroad.

295
00:11:18,444 --> 00:11:20,079
Fans even gave you a nickname

296
00:11:20,146 --> 00:11:22,515
because you love Korean food that much.

297
00:11:22,581 --> 00:11:25,051
They often call me Rice Jin.

298
00:11:25,117 --> 00:11:26,819
-Rice Jin, Yu-jin.
-Yes.

299
00:11:26,886 --> 00:11:31,891
I always make sure I eat rice
even while I'm on a world tour.

300
00:11:31,957 --> 00:11:34,994
And now, let us present…

301
00:11:35,061 --> 00:11:36,829
-Yu-jin's fridge!
-Yu-jin's fridge!

302
00:11:37,496 --> 00:11:39,699
WHY IS EVERYONE CLAPPING?

303
00:11:39,765 --> 00:11:41,867
-Yu-jin's fridge!
-Yu-jin's fridge!

304
00:11:43,669 --> 00:11:44,704
RATHER EMPTY

305
00:11:44,770 --> 00:11:47,073
-It doesn't seem too full.
-Wait.

306
00:11:47,606 --> 00:11:49,175
GETTING EVERYONE TO CHEER

307
00:11:49,575 --> 00:11:51,477
CHEERING ENTHUSIASTICALLY

308
00:11:51,544 --> 00:11:54,013
-That looks amazing.
-I have stuff. I do.

309
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:55,581
It's neatly organized.

310
00:11:55,648 --> 00:11:57,583
-She has nothing.
-She has nothing?

311
00:11:58,584 --> 00:12:00,453
This thing stands out.

312
00:12:00,519 --> 00:12:03,689
What's this?
Is this some kind of preserve?

313
00:12:03,756 --> 00:12:06,625
-Braised chestnuts with the inner skin.
-Braised chestnuts.

314
00:12:06,692 --> 00:12:07,693
Barley chestnuts?

315
00:12:07,760 --> 00:12:09,095
-Braised chestnuts with skin.
-Braised.

316
00:12:09,161 --> 00:12:11,931
Braised chestnuts with skin. What is that?

317
00:12:11,997 --> 00:12:14,200
It's been boiled down
with the inner skin still intact.

318
00:12:14,266 --> 00:12:15,468
BRAISED WITH THE INNER SKIN

319
00:12:15,534 --> 00:12:17,970
Gen Z kids like that.

320
00:12:18,037 --> 00:12:19,638
It adds good flavors.

321
00:12:19,705 --> 00:12:21,373
The skin adds better flavors.

322
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:24,443
I usually like to eat
sweet peeled chestnuts as a snack.

323
00:12:24,510 --> 00:12:25,544
-Chestnuts.
-Sweet chestnuts?

324
00:12:25,611 --> 00:12:28,781
So you like these snacks.
I see them over here.

325
00:12:28,848 --> 00:12:30,750
I was scrolling through short-form content

326
00:12:30,816 --> 00:12:34,120
and found someone making chestnut latte

327
00:12:34,186 --> 00:12:36,489
by using braised chestnuts with skin.

328
00:12:36,555 --> 00:12:38,557
I wanted to try making that,

329
00:12:38,624 --> 00:12:40,159
so I bought it,

330
00:12:40,226 --> 00:12:41,827
but it didn't have much flavor.

331
00:12:41,894 --> 00:12:44,597
It just tasted like sugar.

332
00:12:44,663 --> 00:12:45,765
I don't know what to do with it now.

333
00:12:45,831 --> 00:12:47,500
DON'T KNOW HOW TO USE THIS

334
00:12:47,566 --> 00:12:50,136
-She has another jar.
-You got two jars.

335
00:12:50,202 --> 00:12:52,138
-Those are delicious, though.
-Yes.

336
00:12:52,204 --> 00:12:54,607
What's this? A meal kit?

337
00:12:54,673 --> 00:12:56,675
-A bag of egg whites.
-Egg whites.

338
00:12:56,742 --> 00:12:57,676
Right.

339
00:12:57,743 --> 00:12:59,578
-What?
-Just the whites without the yolk.

340
00:12:59,645 --> 00:13:01,680
-Just the whites?
-I eat it after workouts,

341
00:13:01,747 --> 00:13:03,482
-or for breakfast.
-That's a thing?

342
00:13:03,549 --> 00:13:05,818
-Or in the afternoon.
-The whites are separated

343
00:13:05,885 --> 00:13:08,087
-and formed into egg shapes.
-Is that so?

344
00:13:08,154 --> 00:13:09,855
-It's a part of your diet.
-That's new.

345
00:13:09,922 --> 00:13:11,724
I don't like egg yolk.

346
00:13:11,791 --> 00:13:13,359
-Do you hate it?
-Yes.

347
00:13:13,425 --> 00:13:16,662
I don't like the dry ones,
the ones that are cooked fully.

348
00:13:16,729 --> 00:13:17,863
But that's the best way to have them.

349
00:13:17,930 --> 00:13:20,833
-So I just eat the whites.
-With some soda.

350
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:22,434
-I like to eat those.
-In that case,

351
00:13:22,501 --> 00:13:26,005
how do you usually eat
when you aren't promoting anything?

352
00:13:26,071 --> 00:13:27,907
I love spicy food.

353
00:13:27,973 --> 00:13:30,075
-<i>Malatang</i>?
-Do you enjoy spicy food?

354
00:13:30,142 --> 00:13:31,477
-Braised kimchi.
-Braised kimchi.

355
00:13:31,544 --> 00:13:32,812
-Kimchi-<i>jjigae</i>.
-<i>Jjigae</i>.

356
00:13:32,878 --> 00:13:34,346
Kimchi fried rice.

357
00:13:34,413 --> 00:13:36,182
I like everything made with kimchi.

358
00:13:36,248 --> 00:13:38,818
-She loves kimchi.
-She said she loves Korean food.

359
00:13:38,884 --> 00:13:40,586
My mom makes
the best braised kimchi with pork ribs.

360
00:13:40,653 --> 00:13:43,222
-Braised kimchi with pork ribs.
-Braised kimchi with pork ribs.

361
00:13:43,289 --> 00:13:47,293
I'm realizing that she's more like us.

362
00:13:47,359 --> 00:13:49,795
She has that old dude taste.

363
00:13:49,862 --> 00:13:50,996
She's even cooler.

364
00:13:51,063 --> 00:13:53,332
You sure like spicy food.

365
00:13:53,399 --> 00:13:55,768
-You have some Buldak sauce.
-She has lots.

366
00:13:55,835 --> 00:13:56,836
-What's this?
-Sauce.

367
00:13:56,902 --> 00:13:59,405
-It's made into sticks.
-Smaller portions.

368
00:13:59,471 --> 00:14:02,241
Do you suck on it or what?

369
00:14:02,308 --> 00:14:03,742
ONE STICK PER CRAVING?

370
00:14:03,809 --> 00:14:06,545
-Like a hangover helper?
-Or ginseng extract?

371
00:14:06,612 --> 00:14:07,813
THIS IS HILARIOUS

372
00:14:07,880 --> 00:14:09,248
When I order delivery food,

373
00:14:09,315 --> 00:14:12,451
sometimes I want it to be
more salty or spicy.

374
00:14:12,518 --> 00:14:15,020
-That's when I add some sauce.
-To add spiciness?

375
00:14:15,087 --> 00:14:16,088
You must love spicy food.

376
00:14:16,155 --> 00:14:18,557
-Do you enjoy spicy food?
-I can't handle it.

377
00:14:18,624 --> 00:14:19,892
Me neither.

378
00:14:19,959 --> 00:14:21,794
How much spiciness can you take?

379
00:14:21,861 --> 00:14:24,830
Let's say there are five levels,
with five being the hottest.

380
00:14:24,897 --> 00:14:25,998
Then about level four.

381
00:14:26,065 --> 00:14:28,634
-That's still spicy.
-It must be quite hot.

382
00:14:28,701 --> 00:14:30,569
-So level four for <i>malatang</i>?
-<i>Malatang</i>? Yes.

383
00:14:30,636 --> 00:14:32,404
One level below the maximum spiciness.

384
00:14:32,972 --> 00:14:34,039
SHAKING HEAD

385
00:14:34,106 --> 00:14:36,442
How do you eat your tofu?
Do you like to eat this too?

386
00:14:36,508 --> 00:14:38,377
I've always loved tofu,

387
00:14:38,444 --> 00:14:40,446
and I've recently been eating
pollack roe CTB.

388
00:14:40,512 --> 00:14:42,815
-CTB?
-What's pollack roe CTB?

389
00:14:42,882 --> 00:14:45,150
Pollack roe, cucumber-and-tofu bibimbap.

390
00:14:45,217 --> 00:14:47,086
-I see.
-That's a good one.

391
00:14:47,152 --> 00:14:49,622
Is that a thing?
Or is it your personal creation?

392
00:14:49,688 --> 00:14:50,990
A PERSONAL SMILE

393
00:14:51,056 --> 00:14:52,391
It's not my personal recipe.

394
00:14:52,458 --> 00:14:53,826
It was a short-form content.

395
00:14:53,893 --> 00:14:59,265
There's this person who uploads recipes
for people on a diet.

396
00:14:59,331 --> 00:15:03,602
Put rice, salted pollack roe, cucumber,
and lightly boiled tofu in a bowl,

397
00:15:03,669 --> 00:15:07,072
add some soy sauce and sesame oil,
then mix everything together.

398
00:15:07,139 --> 00:15:08,841
-It's quite nice.
-It sounds good.

399
00:15:08,908 --> 00:15:10,843
Wait, look.

400
00:15:10,910 --> 00:15:13,045
This is an ingredient for Western cuisine.

401
00:15:13,112 --> 00:15:15,047
So you do eat Western food.

402
00:15:15,114 --> 00:15:17,316
It's not that I don't like it.

403
00:15:17,383 --> 00:15:19,218
What's your favorite Western dish?

404
00:15:19,285 --> 00:15:21,553
<i>Meju</i> pasta with pork neck.

405
00:15:21,620 --> 00:15:24,023
-What?
-<i>Meju</i> pasta with pork neck?

406
00:15:24,089 --> 00:15:25,424
<i>Meju</i>? Dried fermented soybeans?

407
00:15:25,491 --> 00:15:28,294
It's a spicy cream pasta

408
00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:30,162
with fermented soybeans, so…

409
00:15:30,229 --> 00:15:32,898
-It sounds good.
-It's a fusion dish.

410
00:15:32,965 --> 00:15:34,800
-Fusion.
-She needs that Korean touch

411
00:15:34,867 --> 00:15:36,235
-even for pasta.
-Just a little.

412
00:15:36,302 --> 00:15:38,270
-A mix.
-Keep that in mind.

413
00:15:38,337 --> 00:15:41,006
We have chefs who cook
Chinese and Japanese cuisine.

414
00:15:41,073 --> 00:15:42,875
Do you like them too?

415
00:15:42,942 --> 00:15:44,910
-I do.
-What kind of Chinese food?

416
00:15:44,977 --> 00:15:46,278
-I like seafood stir-fry.
-Seafood stir-fry?

417
00:15:46,345 --> 00:15:49,214
-Seafood stir-fry?
-You need to eat it with a drink.

418
00:15:49,281 --> 00:15:52,084
I realized that many good-looking girls

419
00:15:52,151 --> 00:15:53,719
tend to have the taste of an old dude.

420
00:15:53,786 --> 00:15:55,254
-Is that so?
-Yes, pretty girls.

421
00:15:55,321 --> 00:15:57,690
-I eat like an old man too.
-You too?

422
00:15:57,756 --> 00:15:59,692
-I eat like an old dude too.
-She wanted to say that.

423
00:15:59,758 --> 00:16:03,128
She has cabbage and cucumbers.

424
00:16:03,195 --> 00:16:04,730
Oyster mushrooms and enoki.

425
00:16:04,797 --> 00:16:06,632
Let's check out the freezer.

426
00:16:06,699 --> 00:16:09,268
-I see some meat.
-Yes, I have some meat.

427
00:16:09,335 --> 00:16:10,402
Pork neck for grilling.

428
00:16:10,469 --> 00:16:13,305
-For <i>meju</i> pasta.
-And this is tenderloin.

429
00:16:13,372 --> 00:16:15,708
For pork, do you prefer neck meat?

430
00:16:15,774 --> 00:16:17,776
Yes, I love the texture.

431
00:16:17,843 --> 00:16:19,211
That slight bite to it.

432
00:16:19,278 --> 00:16:20,279
What are these? Glasses?

433
00:16:21,547 --> 00:16:22,548
Are these glasses?

434
00:16:22,614 --> 00:16:24,483
That's salted pollack roe.

435
00:16:24,550 --> 00:16:26,752
WHY WOULD SHE HAVE GLASSES IN THERE?

436
00:16:26,819 --> 00:16:29,321
I thought these were glasses,
but these were salted pollack roe.

437
00:16:29,388 --> 00:16:31,323
I thought she wanted
to keep her glasses cold.

438
00:16:31,890 --> 00:16:33,625
HAHAHA

439
00:16:33,692 --> 00:16:35,227
<i>Injeolmi</i>.

440
00:16:35,294 --> 00:16:37,396
-You have the taste of an elderly person.
-Those are good.

441
00:16:37,463 --> 00:16:38,464
Fish-shaped buns.

442
00:16:38,530 --> 00:16:39,865
HER TASTE IN SNACKS ARE A BIT…

443
00:16:39,932 --> 00:16:43,168
These are all things that I like.

444
00:16:43,235 --> 00:16:46,472
Wait, your age is…
We have the same kind of taste.

445
00:16:46,538 --> 00:16:48,407
-Hey.
-Hey, look at this.

446
00:16:48,474 --> 00:16:49,842
Where did you get this?

447
00:16:49,908 --> 00:16:50,909
WHAT IS IT?

448
00:16:50,976 --> 00:16:52,111
-It's Ggandori.
-Ggandori.

449
00:16:52,177 --> 00:16:53,178
-Ggandori?
-Chef Hyun-suk.

450
00:16:53,245 --> 00:16:54,580
Ggandori is still around?

451
00:16:54,646 --> 00:16:55,948
What's Ggandori?

452
00:16:56,015 --> 00:16:58,217
-These were 50 won back in the day.
-What? 50 won?

453
00:16:58,283 --> 00:16:59,651
It was a bit wider and flatter.

454
00:16:59,718 --> 00:17:01,286
I didn't have enough money to get one.

455
00:17:01,353 --> 00:17:02,755
HE DIDN'T HAVE 50 WON BACK IN THE DAY…

456
00:17:02,821 --> 00:17:05,491
-Yes, right. It was like 50 won.
-Only rich kids got to eat that.

457
00:17:05,557 --> 00:17:07,860
-You can't find these on the market.
-It's hard to find.

458
00:17:07,926 --> 00:17:09,094
They're not in convenience stores.

459
00:17:09,161 --> 00:17:10,629
Where did you get this?

460
00:17:10,696 --> 00:17:12,364
I ordered them online.

461
00:17:12,431 --> 00:17:13,732
-They're still around?
-Compared to

462
00:17:13,799 --> 00:17:17,136
-the famous red bean ice cream…
-Yes, the hard one.

463
00:17:17,202 --> 00:17:18,771
-…it's much softer.
-It is.

464
00:17:18,837 --> 00:17:22,775
-And its crunchy texture is addictive.
-Yes!

465
00:17:22,841 --> 00:17:25,411
I had this so often
back when I was in grade school.

466
00:17:25,477 --> 00:17:27,880
-Ggandori was a thing before the B brand.
-Yes!

467
00:17:27,946 --> 00:17:30,649
-Don't you know?
-I do. Of course, I do.

468
00:17:30,716 --> 00:17:32,985
Everyone on this side remembers Ggandori.

469
00:17:33,052 --> 00:17:34,286
Have you ever had it?

470
00:17:34,353 --> 00:17:37,489
-Me? I've never seen it before.
-It's my first time too.

471
00:17:37,556 --> 00:17:39,258
Chef Jong-won. Why can't you chime in?

472
00:17:39,324 --> 00:17:41,760
-Yes, why won't you jump in?
-It changed a little.

473
00:17:41,827 --> 00:17:44,630
Don't kids these days
like Dubai hewy cookie?

474
00:17:44,696 --> 00:17:46,432
-What now?
-It's Dubai "chewy" cookie.

475
00:17:46,498 --> 00:17:49,168
-"Dubai hewy cookie"?
-What's hewy?

476
00:17:49,234 --> 00:17:51,837
-It was a slip.
-Is the cookie hewy?

477
00:17:51,904 --> 00:17:55,307
Dubai hewy cookie. Hewy cookies.
So it's called Dubai chewy cookie?

478
00:17:55,374 --> 00:17:57,142
-Yes, DCC.
-Yes, DCC.

479
00:17:57,209 --> 00:17:58,544
-I like that.
-It's too expensive.

480
00:17:58,610 --> 00:18:01,046
But it's too hard to get my hands on it…

481
00:18:01,113 --> 00:18:04,616
-Right.
-…so it fell out of my interest.

482
00:18:04,683 --> 00:18:06,085
So you got Ggandori?

483
00:18:06,151 --> 00:18:07,686
Ggandori is kind of sweet too.

484
00:18:07,753 --> 00:18:10,055
It's just like how old dudes
never eat anything viral.

485
00:18:10,122 --> 00:18:12,791
Old dudes refuse to line up for food.
She's just like that.

486
00:18:12,858 --> 00:18:14,860
-Yes.
-It's too hard to find.

487
00:18:14,927 --> 00:18:17,062
-Just ask her for one later.
-He must want it.

488
00:18:17,129 --> 00:18:18,597
-May I have one?
-Sure.

489
00:18:18,664 --> 00:18:20,466
Let me have a taste… Gosh.

490
00:18:20,532 --> 00:18:22,701
-He's so happy.
-It's been so long.

491
00:18:22,768 --> 00:18:25,737
-Look at the shape.
-It's thinner now.

492
00:18:25,804 --> 00:18:27,539
-Back in the day…
-Was it not like that?

493
00:18:27,606 --> 00:18:29,808
…it was the ordinary flat shape,
but it changed.

494
00:18:29,875 --> 00:18:32,644
-Just one bite.
-Watch your teeth. You might chip one.

495
00:18:32,711 --> 00:18:34,012
FINALLY, THE FIRST BITE

496
00:18:34,079 --> 00:18:35,948
-Does it taste the same?
-Does it?

497
00:18:36,882 --> 00:18:38,851
It still tastes the same!

498
00:18:39,985 --> 00:18:41,120
IT'S STILL THE SAME

499
00:18:41,753 --> 00:18:43,155
CONGRATULATIONS

500
00:18:44,089 --> 00:18:45,324
Chef Hyun-suk, I'm about to cry.

501
00:18:45,991 --> 00:18:47,259
A BITE FOR HIS PEER, HYUN-SUK

502
00:18:47,326 --> 00:18:49,128
-I'm about to cry. It tastes the same.
-Me too.

503
00:18:49,194 --> 00:18:51,396
-The texture is so addictive.
-It is.

504
00:18:51,463 --> 00:18:52,764
-And me.
-Over here.

505
00:18:52,831 --> 00:18:54,166
WHAT ABOUT ME?

506
00:18:56,301 --> 00:18:57,736
WHY WON'T YOU GIVE ME A BITE?

507
00:18:57,803 --> 00:18:59,471
I'm about to cry. It's hard to get these.

508
00:18:59,538 --> 00:19:01,673
You're making me cry too.

509
00:19:01,740 --> 00:19:05,577
I'm going back to those days.
How are you all doing, my buddies?

510
00:19:05,644 --> 00:19:06,812
GETTING EMOTIONAL

511
00:19:07,846 --> 00:19:11,817
I never imagined An Yu-jin's fridge
would bring back my old memories.

512
00:19:11,884 --> 00:19:14,253
Gosh, we found this in An Yu-jin's fridge.

513
00:19:14,319 --> 00:19:16,822
-She doesn't like "An Yu-jin."
-You got too excited.

514
00:19:16,889 --> 00:19:18,357
You should've said "Yu-jin's fridge."

515
00:19:18,423 --> 00:19:21,093
-Yu-jin's fridge.
-I'm sorry. I got too excited.

516
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:23,662
-I even gave you my Ggandori.
-She's right.

517
00:19:23,729 --> 00:19:24,730
I'm sorry, Yu-jin.

518
00:19:24,796 --> 00:19:26,298
How can you repay me like this?

519
00:19:26,365 --> 00:19:29,835
Please let your arms loose.
I'm so sorry, Yu-jin.

520
00:19:29,902 --> 00:19:32,271
I never thought I'd reminisce
while looking through her fridge.

521
00:19:32,337 --> 00:19:34,373
She made everyone emotional.

522
00:19:34,439 --> 00:19:36,575
Next, room temperature stuff.
There's <i>ramyeon</i>.

523
00:19:36,642 --> 00:19:38,810
-Wait, this one says noodle soup.
-It's noodle soup.

524
00:19:38,877 --> 00:19:40,913
Do you see that <i>miyeok-guk</i>,
seaweed soup, in the back?

525
00:19:40,979 --> 00:19:44,616
-This one?
-That recipe was viral for a while.

526
00:19:44,683 --> 00:19:46,785
-It's really good.
-It's Buldak-<i>miyeok</i> noodles.

527
00:19:46,852 --> 00:19:49,588
-Buldak-<i>miyeok</i> noodles?
-You use <i>miyeok-guk</i> as the base,

528
00:19:49,655 --> 00:19:52,024
add a bit of water,
and cook the spicy noodles in it.

529
00:19:52,090 --> 00:19:54,159
It has a deep flavor.

530
00:19:54,226 --> 00:19:55,594
-It's good.
-Wait,

531
00:19:55,661 --> 00:19:57,729
Little Tiger already knows this recipe.

532
00:19:57,796 --> 00:19:58,964
-Of course.
-Yes, born in the 2000s.

533
00:19:59,031 --> 00:20:00,032
Do you know this?

534
00:20:00,098 --> 00:20:02,467
It's perfect for curing hangovers.

535
00:20:02,534 --> 00:20:03,769
A hangover cure.

536
00:20:03,835 --> 00:20:05,771
-It's great with rice too.
-Gen MZ cure hangovers with this?

537
00:20:05,837 --> 00:20:07,873
-I also love spicy food.
-I knew it.

538
00:20:07,940 --> 00:20:09,541
-I see.
-She knows it too.

539
00:20:09,608 --> 00:20:12,311
That was all for Yu-jin's fridge!

540
00:20:12,377 --> 00:20:13,645
CHECKED OUT YU-JIN'S FRIDGE

541
00:20:14,346 --> 00:20:17,149
We met a Gen MZ woman
who eats like an old dude.

542
00:20:17,216 --> 00:20:21,453
I wonder what her orders will be.

543
00:20:21,520 --> 00:20:23,388
Let's find out.

544
00:20:23,455 --> 00:20:24,756
The first one.

545
00:20:24,823 --> 00:20:26,658
-Food for the Old Dude's Taste.
-Food for the Old Dude's Taste.

546
00:20:26,725 --> 00:20:28,126
Food for the Old Dude's Taste.

547
00:20:28,193 --> 00:20:29,761
I'm a part of Gen Z,

548
00:20:29,828 --> 00:20:32,998
-but I do have an old dude's appetite.
-She has an old person's taste in food.

549
00:20:33,065 --> 00:20:35,367
I also love spicy food,

550
00:20:35,434 --> 00:20:37,469
so I want something spicy and hot,

551
00:20:37,536 --> 00:20:40,872
something that resembles Korean cuisine.

552
00:20:40,939 --> 00:20:42,708
-I see.
-So I made that order.

553
00:20:42,774 --> 00:20:45,477
That sounds great.
What's the second order?

554
00:20:45,544 --> 00:20:47,946
-A Snack for Gen MZ.
-A Snack for Gen MZ.

555
00:20:48,013 --> 00:20:49,815
A Snack for Gen MZ?

556
00:20:49,881 --> 00:20:53,719
I want to ask you to make a dessert
that can beat the viral DCC,

557
00:20:53,785 --> 00:20:57,256
although I do not have
enough ingredients in the fridge.

558
00:20:57,322 --> 00:20:59,191
I thought that would be nice.

559
00:20:59,258 --> 00:21:01,927
Your meals are like an old dude,
but you snack like a younger person.

560
00:21:01,994 --> 00:21:05,530
-Yes, I must keep up with the trends.
-That's right.

561
00:21:05,597 --> 00:21:08,667
I have an announcement to make
before the chefs pick out an order.

562
00:21:08,734 --> 00:21:10,035
-What is it?
-Today,

563
00:21:10,102 --> 00:21:12,504
there are nine people here to cook.

564
00:21:12,571 --> 00:21:14,906
That means one of you must sit out.

565
00:21:14,973 --> 00:21:16,575
-What? I see.
-Yes.

566
00:21:16,642 --> 00:21:18,343
One of you must sit out,

567
00:21:18,410 --> 00:21:21,146
but you have to come with us
and do the five-minute check.

568
00:21:21,213 --> 00:21:23,248
I can't do that.

569
00:21:23,315 --> 00:21:24,850
-I'd rather cook.
-You'll sit out,

570
00:21:24,916 --> 00:21:26,952
-but you must work.
-You must earn your keep.

571
00:21:27,019 --> 00:21:28,253
One of you volunteered

572
00:21:28,320 --> 00:21:30,122
-as soon as this was announced.
-Who?

573
00:21:30,188 --> 00:21:32,024
It was Chef Nam-no.

574
00:21:32,090 --> 00:21:33,325
He wants to eat a lot.

575
00:21:33,392 --> 00:21:35,460
He'll devour the food during the check.

576
00:21:35,527 --> 00:21:37,129
-We won't get anything.
-He'll finish it.

577
00:21:37,195 --> 00:21:39,364
-I'll just have a taste.
-He wasn't so good at it last time.

578
00:21:40,499 --> 00:21:43,735
I'll give the first chance
to the two chefs who danced.

579
00:21:43,802 --> 00:21:45,404
Chef Ho-young, you get the first pick.

580
00:21:45,470 --> 00:21:48,006
After all, my specialty
is in Korean cuisine.

581
00:21:48,073 --> 00:21:49,641
-You specialize in Korean food?
-Korean food?

582
00:21:49,708 --> 00:21:51,576
-I even have a license.
-I see.

583
00:21:51,643 --> 00:21:52,644
But not in Japanese.

584
00:21:52,711 --> 00:21:54,680
You little…

585
00:21:54,746 --> 00:21:55,947
THIS IS HOW I HAVE FUN

586
00:21:56,014 --> 00:21:58,850
-I'll take the first order.
-Food for the Old Dude's Taste.

587
00:21:58,917 --> 00:22:01,253
Chef Ho-young chooses
Food for the Old Dude's Taste.

588
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:03,522
Chef Eun-yeong, you're next.

589
00:22:03,588 --> 00:22:06,658
I have an old dude's taste in food too,

590
00:22:06,725 --> 00:22:09,895
and I also want
to chase after Chef Ho-young.

591
00:22:09,961 --> 00:22:11,096
Why are you fighting me?

592
00:22:11,163 --> 00:22:13,765
That means you'll get to cook a dish

593
00:22:13,832 --> 00:22:17,569
that will suit an old dude's taste.
Okay, then.

594
00:22:17,636 --> 00:22:19,838
-A Snack for Gen MZ.
-Dessert?

595
00:22:19,905 --> 00:22:23,141
I want to make
a delicious snack for Yu-jin.

596
00:22:23,208 --> 00:22:25,043
JONG-WON PICKS A SNACK FOR GEN MZ

597
00:22:25,110 --> 00:22:26,645
-Jong-won is in.
-He's making dessert.

598
00:22:26,712 --> 00:22:29,381
And now, who'll take Jong-won down?

599
00:22:29,448 --> 00:22:30,816
Someone should take Jong-won down.

600
00:22:30,882 --> 00:22:33,819
-If he goes down a road…
-Cut it out. I'm serious.

601
00:22:33,885 --> 00:22:36,621
-Jong-won?
-…I want to take the same journey.

602
00:22:36,688 --> 00:22:38,724
And also, I'm a GST,

603
00:22:38,790 --> 00:22:40,959
a Guy who's Serious about Trends.

604
00:22:41,026 --> 00:22:42,861
I watch four hours
of short-form content daily.

605
00:22:42,928 --> 00:22:43,929
GST?

606
00:22:43,995 --> 00:22:45,564
A Guy who's Serious about Taking food?

607
00:22:45,630 --> 00:22:48,467
I always like to keep up with the trend,
so I'll have to join.

608
00:22:48,533 --> 00:22:50,135
-Serious about Trans-fat.
-I know what Gen Zers like.

609
00:22:50,202 --> 00:22:52,337
-Trans-fat?
-Trans-fat?

610
00:22:52,404 --> 00:22:53,872
A GUY WHO'S SERIOUS ABOUT TRANS-FAT

611
00:22:53,939 --> 00:22:55,207
Trans-fat?

612
00:22:56,842 --> 00:22:59,678
Let us begin the first round,
Food for the Old Dude's Taste.

613
00:22:59,745 --> 00:23:03,014
Chef Jung Ho-young
versus Chef Park Eun-yeong!

614
00:23:03,081 --> 00:23:06,218
THE COOK-OFF BEGINS NOW

615
00:23:06,284 --> 00:23:10,622
<i>This is the first cook-off</i>
<i>with ingredients from Yu-jin's fridge.</i>

616
00:23:10,689 --> 00:23:13,425
The two rival performers of the show
are up against each other.

617
00:23:13,492 --> 00:23:17,329
Chef Park Eun-yeong,
someone who has become too manic,

618
00:23:17,396 --> 00:23:19,498
versus someone who has eaten too much,

619
00:23:19,564 --> 00:23:21,666
Chef Jung Ho-young.

620
00:23:21,733 --> 00:23:24,202
Which one of them
is the best performer of the show?

621
00:23:24,269 --> 00:23:27,038
Last time, we held
the <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> Awards,

622
00:23:27,105 --> 00:23:30,008
Since then, Chef Eun-yeong
has been suffering from insomnia.

623
00:23:30,075 --> 00:23:31,410
-Why?
-That's what I heard.

624
00:23:31,476 --> 00:23:32,878
You must've wanted to win

625
00:23:32,944 --> 00:23:34,813
-Best Performance Award that badly.
-Yes.

626
00:23:35,514 --> 00:23:37,082
HER RIVAL, JUNG HO-YOUNG GOT THE AWARD

627
00:23:37,149 --> 00:23:38,483
DEVASTATED

628
00:23:38,550 --> 00:23:40,619
How much more
do I have to dance to get that?

629
00:23:40,685 --> 00:23:44,022
She's too mad to sleep at night.

630
00:23:44,089 --> 00:23:47,626
Actually, I spent the last decade dancing.

631
00:23:47,692 --> 00:23:49,995
-That's true.
-He's pretty much a dancer.

632
00:23:50,061 --> 00:23:52,798
-He built that history.
-He danced even when no one else did.

633
00:23:52,864 --> 00:23:55,700
I continued to dance and dance,
even though no one cared for it.

634
00:23:55,767 --> 00:23:58,236
OH, 10 YEARS…

635
00:23:58,303 --> 00:24:00,906
She can't challenge me
after dancing twice.

636
00:24:00,972 --> 00:24:02,707
-Wasn't this a cooking show?
-Right?

637
00:24:02,774 --> 00:24:04,009
He'll end up on <i>Street Woman Fighter</i>.

638
00:24:04,075 --> 00:24:05,544
Is this <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> or that?

639
00:24:05,610 --> 00:24:09,381
This is more like Street Chef Fighter.

640
00:24:09,448 --> 00:24:11,283
Yu-jin made a polite request today,

641
00:24:11,349 --> 00:24:13,919
that she wanted to see you perform
IVE's dance.

642
00:24:14,719 --> 00:24:16,588
CHEF HO-YOUNG'S INGREDIENTS:
PORK NECK, SALTED POLLACK ROE, TOFU

643
00:24:16,655 --> 00:24:18,824
BULDAK SAUCE, OYSTER MUSHROOM, CABBAGE,
STIR-FRIED KIMCHI, TUNA FISH SAUCE

644
00:24:18,890 --> 00:24:21,560
Chef Ho-young, what are you making?

645
00:24:21,626 --> 00:24:23,795
Here's the name of my dish.

646
00:24:24,396 --> 00:24:27,933
"Old Dude-ya, Dude-ya, Dude-ya."
That's it.

647
00:24:27,999 --> 00:24:31,436
"Old Dude-ya, Dude-ya, Dude-ya."
That's it.

648
00:24:32,704 --> 00:24:33,705
It's "HEYA."

649
00:24:34,105 --> 00:24:37,108
THE MAJESTY OF THE ORIGINAL DANCING FAIRY

650
00:24:37,175 --> 00:24:39,077
Not "HEYA," but Old Dude-ya?

651
00:24:39,144 --> 00:24:41,079
-Dude-ya.
-Old Dude-ya.

652
00:24:41,146 --> 00:24:43,081
<i>Old Dude-ya, Dude-ya, Dude-ya</i>

653
00:24:43,148 --> 00:24:45,050
What's this hand gesture?

654
00:24:45,116 --> 00:24:46,618
Isn't this how the dance ends?

655
00:24:46,685 --> 00:24:48,687
What's the actual dance like?

656
00:24:48,753 --> 00:24:50,255
REMEMBERING…

657
00:24:50,322 --> 00:24:51,490
-Yes, it's there!
-It's there.

658
00:24:51,556 --> 00:24:52,791
It's the same move.

659
00:24:52,858 --> 00:24:55,193
Ho-young has been dancing for a decade.

660
00:24:55,260 --> 00:24:58,230
-He already picked it up in the dance.
-Yes.

661
00:24:58,296 --> 00:24:59,931
I got confused.

662
00:24:59,998 --> 00:25:01,266
What's the dish like?

663
00:25:01,333 --> 00:25:02,834
I'm going to make

664
00:25:02,901 --> 00:25:06,638
a Korean set meal for an old dude's taste,
something Yu-jin will love.

665
00:25:06,705 --> 00:25:10,275
I also eat like an old dude,
so I love dining at drivers' diners.

666
00:25:10,342 --> 00:25:13,945
I'll use pork neck
to make gochujang bulgogi.

667
00:25:14,012 --> 00:25:16,014
YAY, BULGOGI AND RICE

668
00:25:16,081 --> 00:25:17,549
I'll also serve it with some soup

669
00:25:17,616 --> 00:25:19,084
and a little side dish,

670
00:25:19,150 --> 00:25:21,853
as well as some sauce
to top the rice with.

671
00:25:21,920 --> 00:25:23,989
It'll taste refreshingly spicy,

672
00:25:24,055 --> 00:25:26,825
something that you'll love
if you have an old dude's taste.

673
00:25:27,392 --> 00:25:29,494
APPLAUDING WITH ANTICIPATION

674
00:25:29,561 --> 00:25:32,898
-I love it.
-She's already clapping.

675
00:25:33,832 --> 00:25:35,834
CHEF EUN-YEONG'S INGREDIENTS:
SEASONED DRUMSTICK MEAT, TENDERLOIN

676
00:25:35,901 --> 00:25:37,903
CABBAGE, BULDAK SAUCE, ENOKI,
OYSTER MUSHROOM, INSTANT MIYEOK-GUK

677
00:25:37,969 --> 00:25:40,171
What are you making, Chef Eun-yeong?

678
00:25:40,238 --> 00:25:43,408
The name of my dish is…

679
00:25:43,475 --> 00:25:45,243
Hold Your Breath, Love Chicken.

680
00:25:45,310 --> 00:25:47,279
So it's Hold Your Breath, Love Chicken.

681
00:25:47,345 --> 00:25:48,980
I prepared a chicken dish.

682
00:25:49,047 --> 00:25:51,583
The drumsticks you have are already spicy,

683
00:25:51,650 --> 00:25:55,720
but you can take hotter food,
so I'll add more spicy sauce and grill it.

684
00:25:55,787 --> 00:25:58,356
Old dudes who love Chinese food
also love seafood and beef stir-fry,

685
00:25:58,423 --> 00:26:00,091
and you said you loved that too,

686
00:26:00,158 --> 00:26:01,660
so I'll serve it over some rice.

687
00:26:01,726 --> 00:26:03,161
That's going to be tough to beat.

688
00:26:03,228 --> 00:26:06,898
And now, let us begin their cook-off.

689
00:26:06,965 --> 00:26:08,833
<i>He may have short limbs,</i>

690
00:26:08,900 --> 00:26:10,368
<i>but he's built to be the main dancer.</i>

691
00:26:10,435 --> 00:26:12,704
The original dancer, Chef Jung Ho-young.

692
00:26:13,805 --> 00:26:15,273
<i>Her eyes may be dead,</i>

693
00:26:15,340 --> 00:26:17,242
<i>but you know she belongs in the center.</i>

694
00:26:17,309 --> 00:26:20,312
The rising performer, Chef Park Eun-yeong.

695
00:26:20,378 --> 00:26:22,581
A cook-off
between the two performers of the show!

696
00:26:22,647 --> 00:26:24,950
Who's going to take the honor
as the best performer?

697
00:26:25,016 --> 00:26:28,753
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

698
00:26:31,823 --> 00:26:33,258
All right!

699
00:26:33,325 --> 00:26:34,326
Oh, gosh.

700
00:26:34,392 --> 00:26:35,594
THE MOST NERVOUS ONE HERE

701
00:26:36,061 --> 00:26:38,530
CAPTURE HER OLD DUDE'S TASTE

702
00:26:38,597 --> 00:26:40,432
You must capture her taste,
the old dude's taste.

703
00:26:40,498 --> 00:26:41,733
She starts the fire first.

704
00:26:41,800 --> 00:26:43,602
She's grilling that right away.

705
00:26:43,668 --> 00:26:45,737
-Is that chicken breast?
-On a gridiron.

706
00:26:45,804 --> 00:26:47,672
Isn't that already seasoned?

707
00:26:47,739 --> 00:26:49,374
I'll add some more sauce.

708
00:26:49,441 --> 00:26:51,643
You're adding more sauce?

709
00:26:51,710 --> 00:26:54,546
Chef Eun-yeong said
she'd make seafood and beef stir-fry,

710
00:26:54,613 --> 00:26:58,083
while Chef Ho-young said
he'd make pork neck bulgogi and rice.

711
00:26:58,850 --> 00:27:01,786
-Soy sauce and cooking wine?
-Cooking wine and tuna fish sauce.

712
00:27:01,853 --> 00:27:04,222
-Is that red pepper powder?
-It's the bulgogi sauce.

713
00:27:04,990 --> 00:27:06,725
-Are you making the sauce?
-Yes.

714
00:27:07,292 --> 00:27:09,761
-Sugar.
-Wow.

715
00:27:09,828 --> 00:27:11,196
GRIND EVERYTHING

716
00:27:11,262 --> 00:27:13,098
-It grinds quickly.
-"I wish 'someone' would hold it."

717
00:27:13,164 --> 00:27:14,799
He's making gochujang bulgogi sauce.

718
