She's coughing and choking.

1897
01:11:45,467 --> 01:11:47,002
-It's caught in her throat!
-What happened?

1898
01:11:47,069 --> 01:11:48,504
-It's an emergency.
-Come on.

1899
01:11:48,570 --> 01:11:50,506
-It's an emergency.
-Come on.

1900
01:11:50,572 --> 01:11:53,275
She must've inhaled something.

1901
01:11:53,909 --> 01:11:56,779
I ended up coughing
while trying to take a big gulp.

1902
01:11:56,845 --> 01:11:59,548
I didn't know this was a warm drink.

1903
01:11:59,615 --> 01:12:01,550
-It is?
-It's a warm drink.

1904
01:12:01,617 --> 01:12:03,719
-I thought it was cold.
-I made it warm.

1905
01:12:03,786 --> 01:12:05,688
It's perfect for the winter.

1906
01:12:05,754 --> 01:12:07,456
-It's like Einstein.
-Chestnuts.

1907
01:12:07,523 --> 01:12:09,258
-Einspanner.
-Einstein?

1908
01:12:09,325 --> 01:12:11,026
DID YOU SAY EINSTEIN?

1909
01:12:11,393 --> 01:12:12,695
-Einspanner.
-Einspanner.

1910
01:12:12,761 --> 01:12:14,363
Yes, it's like that.

1911
01:12:14,430 --> 01:12:15,831
OLD DUDES ONLY RECALL HALF OF THE WORD

1912
01:12:16,065 --> 01:12:19,902
This is exactly the kind of beverage
that isn't too sweet, just as I wanted.

1913
01:12:19,968 --> 01:12:22,438
I wanted to try making
something like this,

1914
01:12:22,504 --> 01:12:24,039
something that tastes like this.

1915
01:12:24,106 --> 01:12:26,342
Isn't it sweet
with the whipped cream and all?

1916
01:12:26,408 --> 01:12:27,609
It's not too sweet, actually.

1917
01:12:27,676 --> 01:12:29,311
He added milk foam--

1918
01:12:29,378 --> 01:12:31,580
In the middle.
Then he topped it with cream.

1919
01:12:31,647 --> 01:12:35,084
There's a layer of foam, not just cream.
That's why it's not as greasy.

1920
01:12:35,150 --> 01:12:37,119
-The cream melts into the hot drink…
-Yes, it does.

1921
01:12:37,186 --> 01:12:38,687
…so he left the foam in the middle.

1922
01:12:38,754 --> 01:12:39,755
LEARNED SOMETHING NEW

1923
01:12:39,822 --> 01:12:40,889
Let the chefs explain the dishes now.

1924
01:12:40,956 --> 01:12:42,324
THE ARTIST CAN RELAX

1925
01:12:42,391 --> 01:12:43,726
Go ahead!

1926
01:12:43,792 --> 01:12:46,362
-I explained so much today.
-You need to take a break.

1927
01:12:46,428 --> 01:12:48,030
You've done enough with "Einstein."
No more.

1928
01:12:48,464 --> 01:12:50,232
AGREED

1929
01:12:50,299 --> 01:12:52,101
Tell us about the <i>yul-ran</i>.

1930
01:12:52,167 --> 01:12:55,838
-The <i>yul-ran</i> extremely soft.
-It must be.

1931
01:12:55,904 --> 01:12:59,675
That's why it tastes really great
when you have it with a beverage.

1932
01:12:59,742 --> 01:13:02,010
-Does it melt?
-Yes, it really does.

1933
01:13:02,077 --> 01:13:03,712
-It's so good.
-It's about the texture.

1934
01:13:03,779 --> 01:13:05,514
-Next to it is <i>chalpyeon</i>.
-Yes.

1935
01:13:05,581 --> 01:13:08,450
I topped it with some apple
and put fig jam in the middle.

1936
01:13:08,517 --> 01:13:10,152
-Apple and fig jam.
-And steamed it, right?

1937
01:13:10,219 --> 01:13:11,687
Yes, so she can taste
a variety of flavors.

1938
01:13:11,754 --> 01:13:13,255
-Try the middle.
-Can she pull it apart?

1939
01:13:13,322 --> 01:13:15,190
-Should I eat it in one bite?
-That's probably better.

1940
01:13:15,257 --> 01:13:16,258
I'll have it in one bite.

1941
01:13:16,325 --> 01:13:18,560
The fig jam in the middle
will burst inside your mouth.

1942
01:13:18,627 --> 01:13:21,997
-<i>If it's okay with you, that is.</i>
-<i>I can do it.</i>

1943
01:13:22,498 --> 01:13:23,999
-Let me try it.
-Please try it.

1944
01:13:24,066 --> 01:13:25,634
This is <i>chalpyeon</i>, glutinous rice cake.

1945
01:13:25,701 --> 01:13:27,136
It looks good.

1946
01:13:27,202 --> 01:13:29,204
He made it with chestnut and apple.

1947
01:13:29,271 --> 01:13:30,939
SHE SMILES AS SOON AS SHE CHEWS

1948
01:13:31,874 --> 01:13:33,242
My dish is getting colder.

1949
01:13:34,777 --> 01:13:36,678
She must like it.

1950
01:13:36,745 --> 01:13:37,746
-And?
-The latte.

1951
01:13:37,813 --> 01:13:39,014
-It's like watching an ad.
-A warm drink.

1952
01:13:40,883 --> 01:13:42,584
PRETTY, CUTE, FACE CARD HITTING HARD

1953
01:13:42,651 --> 01:13:43,652
SUDDENLY FEELING SHY

1954
01:13:44,019 --> 01:13:46,455
SHE MAKES EVERYONE HAPPY WITH HER MAGIC

1955
01:13:46,522 --> 01:13:47,723
She's like a kitty.

1956
01:13:48,190 --> 01:13:49,458
THIS ONE'S JUST AN UNFORTUNATE LEOPARD CAT

1957
01:13:49,525 --> 01:13:51,427
-Is it a Beautiful Chest-Night?
-Yu-jin does it.

1958
01:13:51,493 --> 01:13:53,095
-It is beautiful.
-Is it?

1959
01:13:53,162 --> 01:13:55,964
The apple on top goes well with it too.

1960
01:13:56,031 --> 01:13:57,032
Ahem.

1961
01:13:57,099 --> 01:14:00,202
Then next, Chef Sung-jun's DCP.

1962
01:14:00,569 --> 01:14:01,970
REFRESHING AND SWEET FIG CREAM CHEESE

1963
01:14:02,938 --> 01:14:07,242
FLUFFY SOUFFLÉ PANCAKES
WITH CRISPY CHESTNUT KADAYIF

1964
01:14:08,210 --> 01:14:11,113
CHEF KWON SUNG-JUN'S DCP

1965
01:14:11,180 --> 01:14:14,416
It's called DCP, made by Chef Sung-jun.

1966
01:14:14,483 --> 01:14:16,351
May I pour a cup of water
before you try mine?

1967
01:14:16,418 --> 01:14:17,920
Why? To rinse her palate?

1968
01:14:17,986 --> 01:14:19,221
-I got water.
-Why?

1969
01:14:19,288 --> 01:14:21,290
What is that? Is that limewater?

1970
01:14:21,657 --> 01:14:23,425
SUSPICIOUS, CLOUDY WATER

1971
01:14:23,492 --> 01:14:26,228
-When it comes to design, I mean, dessert…
-"Design"?

1972
01:14:26,295 --> 01:14:27,396
Is that soap water?

1973
01:14:27,463 --> 01:14:29,064
-It's not.
-Is that dish soap?

1974
01:14:29,131 --> 01:14:31,066
-What is that?
-What is this?

1975
01:14:31,133 --> 01:14:32,401
It's lemon water.

1976
01:14:32,468 --> 01:14:34,803
To cleanse your palate of the fats
from the chestnuts you had

1977
01:14:34,870 --> 01:14:35,871
and enjoy my dessert.

1978
01:14:35,938 --> 01:14:37,773
-"Only taste my food."
-That's it.

1979
01:14:37,840 --> 01:14:39,208
-Just my food.
-It's edible, right?

1980
01:14:39,274 --> 01:14:42,010
-It's not my dish. It's just lemon water.
-Is it really?

1981
01:14:42,077 --> 01:14:44,346
It gets murky, but it clears soon enough.
Did you put soap in it?

1982
01:14:44,413 --> 01:14:45,380
FALSE CHARGES

1983
01:14:45,447 --> 01:14:47,216
Will she emit bubbles after drinking that?

1984
01:14:47,282 --> 01:14:48,717
Emit bubbles?

1985
01:14:48,784 --> 01:14:50,586
SLANDER EVERYWHERE

1986
01:14:50,652 --> 01:14:52,921
-May I explain this?
-He's quite desperate.

1987
01:14:54,089 --> 01:14:55,858
-I made these soufflé pancakes…
-Yes?

1988
01:14:55,924 --> 01:14:57,860
…after finding out that you like
an egg confectionery in Hong Kong.

1989
01:14:57,926 --> 01:15:00,696
-That's right.
-So I wanted to make something similar.

1990
01:15:00,762 --> 01:15:01,897
The pancake is just sweet,

1991
01:15:01,964 --> 01:15:05,067
so when you get sick of that,
try it with some fig cream cheese.

1992
01:15:05,133 --> 01:15:06,969
Since when did you
come all the way here to explain the dish?

1993
01:15:07,035 --> 01:15:09,338
-Only when I'm desperate.
-He's desperate.

1994
01:15:09,404 --> 01:15:12,040
-He's desperate. He needs to win.
-He's desperate.

1995
01:15:12,107 --> 01:15:13,609
All right.

1996
01:15:13,675 --> 01:15:15,844
-Try it.
-This is DCP.

1997
01:15:15,911 --> 01:15:18,814
-DCP.
-It was so good when I had it.

1998
01:15:18,881 --> 01:15:20,516
It's all about that texture.

1999
01:15:20,582 --> 01:15:22,284
-He made three layers.
-I did.

2000
01:15:22,351 --> 01:15:24,319
It's a contrast
of softness and crunchiness.

2001
01:15:24,386 --> 01:15:25,487
PERFECTION

2002
01:15:25,554 --> 01:15:27,456
There's moisture in the chestnut.

2003
01:15:27,523 --> 01:15:29,892
It's all over if the kadayif turned soggy.

2004
01:15:29,958 --> 01:15:30,959
-Without the crunchiness?
-Yes.

2005
01:15:31,026 --> 01:15:33,128
-I hope it's okay.
-I hope it's crunchy.

2006
01:15:33,195 --> 01:15:34,663
I'm a bit nervous too.

2007
01:15:34,730 --> 01:15:35,998
It looks delicious, though.

2008
01:15:36,064 --> 01:15:37,266
It looks good.

2009
01:15:37,933 --> 01:15:39,968
WELL?

2010
01:15:42,070 --> 01:15:44,139
It must be soft.

2011
01:15:44,206 --> 01:15:45,474
What about the kadayif?

2012
01:15:45,541 --> 01:15:48,110
-It has to be crunchy.
-We need to hear it.

2013
01:15:48,944 --> 01:15:50,112
MMM!

2014
01:15:50,178 --> 01:15:52,614
She must be feeling lots of textures.

2015
01:15:52,681 --> 01:15:54,116
As soon as you take a bite,

2016
01:15:54,182 --> 01:15:57,519
-at first, it's soft due to the pancakes.
-It must be soft.

2017
01:15:57,586 --> 01:16:00,322
Then something
near my molar goes, "Crisp."

2018
01:16:00,389 --> 01:16:03,825
-I see.
-I can feel the crispiness on the inside.

2019
01:16:06,194 --> 01:16:08,297
Is it as crunchy as DCC?

2020
01:16:08,363 --> 01:16:10,165
Is it not as crunchy?

2021
01:16:10,232 --> 01:16:11,967
It's about half as much.

2022
01:16:12,034 --> 01:16:13,435
THE CRISPINESS GOT HALVED

2023
01:16:13,502 --> 01:16:15,437
-The fig cream cheese.
-I love the chestnut cream.

2024
01:16:15,504 --> 01:16:17,339
-Right?
-Yes.

2025
01:16:17,406 --> 01:16:18,740
LOTS OF CHESTNUT CREAM

2026
01:16:18,807 --> 01:16:20,275
-It looks good.
-I'll try it with cream cheese.

2027
01:16:20,342 --> 01:16:21,343
-Wow.
-It looks good.

2028
01:16:21,410 --> 01:16:22,444
LOTS OF FIG CREAM CHEESE

2029
01:16:22,511 --> 01:16:24,713
-This can't be not good.
-Yes.

2030
01:16:24,780 --> 01:16:25,981
GUARANTEED DELICIOUSNESS

2031
01:16:27,215 --> 01:16:28,216
NOM

2032
01:16:28,283 --> 01:16:29,484
She eats so neatly.

2033
01:16:30,152 --> 01:16:31,553
MMM

2034
01:16:31,620 --> 01:16:33,255
Is it better with the cream cheese?

2035
01:16:35,624 --> 01:16:37,059
CELEBRATING HIS OWN SUCCESS

2036
01:16:37,125 --> 01:16:38,594
Why are you clapping for yourself?

2037
01:16:40,028 --> 01:16:41,863
-It's a mistake.
-That's a mistake.

2038
01:16:41,930 --> 01:16:43,999
It's even better with the cream cheese.

2039
01:16:44,066 --> 01:16:45,734
I like both,

2040
01:16:45,801 --> 01:16:49,471
but it's much better
when I eat it with lots of chestnut cream.

2041
01:16:50,238 --> 01:16:53,508
-She really loves the chestnut cream.
-You needed lots of cream.

2042
01:16:53,575 --> 01:16:57,312
You captured her heart in many ways,
and she gave you a thumbs-up.

2043
01:16:57,779 --> 01:16:59,514
CHESTNUT LATTE

2044
01:16:59,581 --> 01:17:00,983
Wait, she reaches for the latte.

2045
01:17:01,049 --> 01:17:02,417
It's all right.

2046
01:17:02,784 --> 01:17:04,553
UGH…

2047
01:17:04,620 --> 01:17:07,222
-Can she try the chestnut latte?
-Of course.

2048
01:17:07,289 --> 01:17:08,957
The latte must be good.

2049
01:17:09,024 --> 01:17:10,692
It must be good.

2050
01:17:11,326 --> 01:17:13,629
LOOKING PLEASED AS SHE WRAPS UP

2051
01:17:15,430 --> 01:17:17,699
-What do I do?
-It's time to choose.

2052
01:17:17,766 --> 01:17:20,268
<i>Press one for Jong-won.</i>

2053
01:17:20,335 --> 01:17:22,471
<i>Press two for Sung-jun.</i>

2054
01:17:22,537 --> 01:17:23,739
Please make your decision.

2055
01:17:23,805 --> 01:17:25,040
What do I do?

2056
01:17:25,107 --> 01:17:28,010
-And press… the button!
-This is too hard.

2057
01:17:29,011 --> 01:17:30,779
NOT MY CHOICE
JUST HAVING FUN

2058
01:17:31,413 --> 01:17:33,015
All right.

2059
01:17:33,081 --> 01:17:34,650
YU-JIN HAVING TROUBLE MAKING A CHOICE

2060
01:17:34,716 --> 01:17:36,618
She chose quickly in the previous round.

2061
01:17:36,685 --> 01:17:38,387
This one is taking her a while.

2062
01:17:38,453 --> 01:17:41,289
Which snack will it be?

2063
01:17:41,356 --> 01:17:42,357
She pressed one.

2064
01:17:42,424 --> 01:17:44,192
-Okay.
-She made her choice.

2065
01:17:44,259 --> 01:17:46,495
Let's find out Yu-jin's choice.

2066
01:17:46,561 --> 01:17:47,562
Show us!

2067
01:17:48,296 --> 01:17:50,599
A Snack for Gen MZ.

2068
01:17:50,666 --> 01:17:53,835
Will Sung-jun beat Jong-won

2069
01:17:53,902 --> 01:17:55,337
and take his second star?

2070
01:17:55,904 --> 01:17:58,540
Or will Chef Jong-won win

2071
01:17:58,607 --> 01:18:01,576
and leave Sung-jun far behind?

2072
01:18:01,643 --> 01:18:04,046
Which one did Yu-jin choose?

2073
01:18:04,713 --> 01:18:07,783
Which snack did you like better?

2074
01:18:07,849 --> 01:18:09,851
Which snack did you like better?

2075
01:18:09,918 --> 01:18:11,453
Show us!

2076
01:18:11,520 --> 01:18:12,487
Show us!

2077
01:18:14,022 --> 01:18:15,223
SON JONG-WON WINS

2078
01:18:15,290 --> 01:18:16,725
Son Jong-won wins.

2079
01:18:16,792 --> 01:18:19,428
CHEF SON JONG-WON'S
IT'S A BEAUTIFUL CHEST-NIGHT WINS

2080
01:18:19,494 --> 01:18:20,896
Jong-won wins.

2081
01:18:21,096 --> 01:18:22,631
LOST HEART

2082
01:18:22,698 --> 01:18:23,732
It's an emergency.

2083
01:18:24,132 --> 01:18:26,234
SUNG-JUN EMERGENCY

2084
01:18:26,301 --> 01:18:28,603
Nothing is working out for him.
It's an emergency.

2085
01:18:28,670 --> 01:18:30,472
He did everything he could today.

2086
01:18:30,539 --> 01:18:32,841
He used every move he could.

2087
01:18:33,575 --> 01:18:35,777
I thought DCP looked delicious.

2088
01:18:35,844 --> 01:18:37,979
I really loved the idea
behind this dessert.

2089
01:18:38,046 --> 01:18:39,948
I loved it,

2090
01:18:40,015 --> 01:18:41,983
but while eating this,

2091
01:18:42,050 --> 01:18:43,251
I found myself

2092
01:18:43,318 --> 01:18:46,288
keep reaching for this drink.

2093
01:18:46,354 --> 01:18:47,689
That must've been the key.

2094
01:18:47,756 --> 01:18:52,194
I think that was the difference
that made me side with Chef Jong-won.

2095
01:18:52,861 --> 01:18:54,696
-That's the reason.
-I see.

2096
01:18:54,763 --> 01:18:55,964
He should've made a beverage.

2097
01:18:56,031 --> 01:18:57,733
-Any thoughts, Sung-jun?
-I missed that.

2098
01:18:57,799 --> 01:18:59,434
BEVERAGE MISS

2099
01:18:59,501 --> 01:19:02,704
And so, Chef Jong-won

2100
01:19:02,771 --> 01:19:05,407
takes his third star
and continues to seize the lead.

2101
01:19:05,474 --> 01:19:07,109
Please put a star on him.

2102
01:19:07,175 --> 01:19:09,010
-He's marching forward.
-He is.

2103
01:19:09,578 --> 01:19:10,579
It's his third win.

2104
01:19:10,645 --> 01:19:11,847
He's in the lead.

2105
01:19:11,913 --> 01:19:14,449
Congratulations.
It's a Beautiful Chest-Night!

2106
01:19:14,516 --> 01:19:17,085
-Thank you.
-Congratulations!

2107
01:19:17,152 --> 01:19:18,887
Jong-won takes his third win.

2108
01:19:19,454 --> 01:19:22,758
Jin-young has been working
both as an actor and a singer.

2109
01:19:22,824 --> 01:19:25,160
He was even nicknamed
the chart-climbing soldier.

2110
01:19:25,227 --> 01:19:26,328
-How cool.
-You're ripped.

2111
01:19:26,394 --> 01:19:27,729
I gained some weight

2112
01:19:27,796 --> 01:19:28,997
and became 80 kg,

2113
01:19:29,064 --> 01:19:30,298
so I had to drop 10 kilograms.

2114
01:19:30,365 --> 01:19:31,733
Why did you lose weight at 80 kg?

2115
01:19:31,800 --> 01:19:33,368
You're going to be anemic.

2116
01:19:34,002 --> 01:19:35,904
You'll feel dizzy when you reach 80 kg.

2117
01:19:35,971 --> 01:19:37,239
He eats so well.

2118
01:19:37,305 --> 01:19:38,740
I want to steal it from him.

2119
01:19:38,807 --> 01:19:40,008
The rivals with history.

2120
01:19:40,342 --> 01:19:42,177
A WINNING MOVE, HOT STONE POT RICE

2121
01:19:42,477 --> 01:19:43,478
IT LOOKS SO GOOD

2122
01:19:43,545 --> 01:19:45,147
He's using a fan to put on a show!

2123
01:19:45,213 --> 01:19:47,215
Hyun-suk seizes the round
just as he always does.

2124
01:19:47,749 --> 01:19:49,084
What's it like?

2125
01:19:49,151 --> 01:19:50,519
It tastes so wonderful!

2126
01:19:50,585 --> 01:19:52,287
It tastes so wonderful!

2127
01:19:52,354 --> 01:19:54,923
Road to Kim Poong,
the long-awaited first round.

2128
01:19:55,423 --> 01:19:57,092
THE COOK OF THE DARKNESS ROARS

2129
01:19:57,159 --> 01:19:58,894
<i>I may not seem like much,</i>
<i>but I'm still a tiger.</i>

2130
01:19:58,960 --> 01:20:00,395
<i>She's like a tiger when she cooks.</i>

2131
01:20:00,462 --> 01:20:01,663
BUT HIS DARK ENERGY ATTACKS

2132
01:20:01,730 --> 01:20:02,731
AN UNEXPECTED SITUATION

2133
01:20:02,798 --> 01:20:03,732
Why is he doing this?

2134
01:20:03,799 --> 01:20:06,101
We're seeing the second
Poongphobia patient in the making.

2135
01:20:06,168 --> 01:20:07,335
SCREAMING

2136
01:20:07,402 --> 01:20:09,471
CAN SHE STAY STRONG UNTIL THE END?

2137
01:20:13,108 --> 01:20:16,011
What am I going to do?
I'm more nervous now than at <i>CCW2</i>.

2138
01:20:16,077 --> 01:20:18,246
It's all right.

2139
01:20:27,789 --> 01:20:32,794
Subtitle translation by: Eunsook Youn
